        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Just thought I'd mention something.</P><P>There has been a lot of debate going around for a long time about how the 59 pet compares to any of the others.</P><P>I'll tell you what I've learned from my experience...</P><P>When dueling another necromancer with various pet combinations I found that the Emissary of Thule pet has approximately 2400 hp.  I added up all the hits scored against it by the other pet until it died, and it took around 2400 hitpoints to kill it, give or take just a few.</P><P>Then, dueled the spectre against the monk.  It killed the monk pet with half of it's health left.  The damage it did to the monk to kill it was about 1300 hp.</P><P>So what this essentially means is that the spectre's damage output is similar to the monks, deduced from the fact that the spectre dealt out 1300 hitpoints damage killing the monk pet during the same time that the monk dealt out 1200 hitpoints damage getting the spectre to half health.</P><P>To me, this seems pretty nice, and a decent upgrade.  I will not argue the fact, however, that in most situations I will use it in it will still be painfully inadequate.  Most recent uber mob I attended had a 1250 damage area effect spell that went off what seemed like every 20 seconds, so at most this pet will live for 40 seconds even if I try to heal him...</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
